law.text: Nothing in this chapter shall restrict or limit in any manner the authority and duty of any regulating board of competent jurisdiction to license individual persons rendering professional services or to regulate the practice of the profession which is within the jurisdiction of such regulating board, even though such person is an officer, director, shareholder, or employee of a professional service corporation or engages in the practice of such profession through a professional service corporation.
law.history: Repealed and reenacted 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 51, sec. 90, effective July 15, 2010. -- Amended 2007 Ky. Acts ch. 137, sec. 90, effective June 26, 2007. -- Created 1962 Ky. Acts ch. 236, sec. 7.

metadata.lrc-note: (7/15/2010). 2010 Ky. Acts ch. 51, sec. 183, provides, "The specific textual provisions of Sections 1 to 178 of this Act which reflect amendments made to those sections by 2007 Ky. Acts ch. 137 shall be deemed effective as of June 26, 2007, and those provisions are hereby made expressly retroactive to that date, with the remainder of the text of those sections being unaffected by the provisions of this section."
